People, I'm using others pack of OnOne PlugIns, but they use the same keygen by RedT, @tosotm give the correct instructions, I'm gonna me it clear.

1. Install the PlugIn
2. Click 'License>' button
3. Put the this 18 sn: 709348-579341-227123
4. Now click 'Manual Activation'
5. Run keygen from RedT folder
6. Copy the 15 sn to 'Unlock Code' field
7. Click 'Activate'. Done!

This worked for me for PhotoTools and PhotoTune, i think that the process is the same for all OnOne Plugins that ask for activation.

This is what I did after several times of trying:
1-unrared iso file-"extract here"

3-when done, enter 123456-123456-123456 or the other listed..same same.
4-it asks for unlock code, so open the keygen..yes, it's not an ordinary keygen where it constantly spits out new numbers. type that number in. copy paste didn't work for me I had 6x3 numbers so I was ok. others noted they had 15 numbers. I just right click the keygen "run as" then I checked only the top button. manually activate. With some software you have to either block internet or block through firewal, neither apply here.
5-copy the dll file over from the redT to the plugin folder in PS. I used it with cs4..
6-when launched with cs4 it has it's own tab "onone" next to "window" and runs from there. it asked me if I want an update for cs5 compatability..no thank you..I only ran focal point and it works fine.will play with it some more..BRAVO and thanks for the upload..
